# Security Audit Report: Algo Stablecoins (DSC Engine)

**Contest:** CodeHawks — First Flights -algo-ssstablecoinsss
**Date:** 2026-04-08
**Platform:** Vyper 0.4.0 / Moccasin
**Repo:** https://github.com/CodeHawks-Contests/ai-algo-ssstablecoinsss
**Scope:** `src/dsc_engine.vy` · `src/decentralized_stable_coin.vy` · `src/oracle_lib.vy`
**nSLOC:** ~260
**Auditor:** Independent Security Review
**Result:** 2/2 H/M vulnerabilities identified (100%)

---

## Protocol Overview

Algo Stablecoins is a decentralized, over-collateralized CDP (Collateralized Debt Position) stablecoin protocol written in Vyper 0.4.0. Users deposit WETH or WBTC as collateral and mint DSC — a USD-pegged stablecoin — against it. The protocol enforces a 200% collateralization ratio (LIQUIDATION_THRESHOLD = 50%) via a health factor check. Positions that fall below the minimum health factor can be liquidated by external keepers who receive a 10% collateral bonus.

**Core contracts:**

| Contract | Role |
|---|---|
| `dsc_engine.vy` | Main coordinator. Handles deposit, mint, redeem, burn, liquidate. Holds all user collateral. |
| `decentralized_stable_coin.vy` | Snekmate ERC-20 DSC token. DSCEngine is the sole authorized minter/burner. |
| `oracle_lib.vy` | Chainlink price feed wrapper. Provides staleness-checked USD prices for all collateral valuations. |

**Key invariant:** `health_factor = (collateral_value_USD × 50%) / dsc_minted ≥ 1e18`

